specJson.name: brightics.function.textanalytics$tokenizer_eng
specJson.label: Tokenizer (English)
specJson.description:
Tokenization is the process of demarcating and possibly classifying sections of a string of input characters. The resulting tokens are then passed on to some other form of processing. The process can be considered a sub-task of parsing input.

In corpus linguistics, part-of-speech tagging (POS tagging or PoS tagging or POST), also called grammatical tagging or word-category disambiguation, is the process of marking up a word in a text (corpus) as corresponding to a particular part of speech, based on both its definition and its context—i.e., its relationship with adjacent and related words in a phrase, sentence, or paragraph. A simplified form of this is commonly taught to school-age children, in the identification of words as nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, etc.

Reference: 
+ <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lexical_analysis#Tokenization>
+ <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Part-of-speech_tagging>

specJson.summary: This function tokenizes english string data into parts of speech(POS).

md:
# Tokenizer (English) This function tokenizes english string data into parts of speech(POS). ## Description Tokenization is the process of demarcating and possibly classifying sections of a string of input characters. The resulting tokens are then passed on to some other form of processing. The process can be considered a sub-task of parsing input. In corpus linguistics, part-of-speech tagging (POS tagging or PoS tagging or POST), also called grammatical tagging or word-category disambiguation, is the process of marking up a word in a text (corpus) as corresponding to a particular part of speech, based on both its definition and its context—i.e., its relationship with adjacent and related words in a phrase, sentence, or paragraph. A simplified form of this is commonly taught to school-age children, in the identification of words as nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, etc. Reference: + + ## Properties ### VA #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Text data in a Table. #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Output Table. It contain input table's columns and tokenized text column. #### PARAMETER 1. **Input Columns***: Columns to select as input. Only String type columns are possible. 2. **Hold Columns**: Result table includes hold columns in input table as well as the result of the operation. If None, all columns are included. 3. **New Column Prefix**: Name of the new column to be added. 4. **Stemming**: Whether to use stemming; the process of reducing inflected words to their word stem, base or root form. - Available Options : `True`, `False` 5. **Extraction**: Extraction of items to return. - Available Options : `Coordinating Conjunction`, `Cardinal Digit`, `Determiner`, `Existential There`, `Foreign Word`, `Preposition/Subordinating Conjunction`, `Adjective`, `Adjective, Comparative`, `Adjective, Superlative`, `List Marker`, `Modal`, `Noun, Singular`, `Noun Plural`, `Proper Noun, Singular`, `Proper Noun, Plural`, `Predeterminer`, `Possessive Ending`, `Personal Pronoun`, `Possessive Pronoun`, `Adverb`, `Adverb, Comparative`, `Adverb, Superlative`, `Particle`, `To`, `Interjection`, `Verb, Base`, `Verb, Past Tense`, `Verb, Gerund/Present Participle`, `Verb, Past Participle`, `Verb, Sing. Present, Non-3d`, `Verb, 3rd Person Sing. Present`, `Wh-determiner`, `Wh-pronoun`, `Possessive Wh-pronoun`, `Wh-abverb` 6. **Power of Speech Tagging**: Whether to show parts of speech with tokenized words. - Available Options : `True`, `False` ### Python #### USAGE ``` tokenizer_eng(table, input_cols, hold_cols=None, new_col_prefix='tokenized', stemming=True, pos_extraction=None, is_tagged=False) ``` #### INPUT 1. **table***: (Table) Text data in a Table. #### OUTPUT 1. **out_table**: (Table) Output Table. It contain input table's columns and tokenized text column. #### PARAMETER 1. **input_cols***: Columns to select as input. Only String type columns are possible. * Type: *list[str]* 2. **hold_cols**: Result table includes hold columns in input table as well as the result of the operation. If None, all columns are included. * Type: *list[str]* 3. **new_col_prefix**: Name of the new column to be added. * Type: *str* * Default / Range: 'tokenized' 4. **stemming**: Whether to use stemming; the process of reducing inflected words to their word stem, base or root form. * Type: *bool* * Default / Range: False 5. **pos_extraction**: Extraction of items to return. * Type: *list[str]* * Default / Range: CC ( CC | CD | DT | EX | FW | INJJ | JJJJR | JJRJJS | JJS | LS | MDNN | NNNNS | NNSNNP | NNPNNPS | NNPS | PDT | POS | PRP | PRP$RB | RBRBR | RBRRBS | RBS | RP | TO | UHVB | VBVBD | VBD | VBGVBN | VBNVBP | VBPVBZ | VBZ | WDT | WP | WP$ | WRB ) 6. **is_tagged**: Whether to show parts of speech with tokenized words. * Type: *bool* * Default value: False ## Example ### VA **[Sample Model]**
In this tutorial workflow, simple text data Table created by Create Table function are used as input of Tokenizer(English) function. The output of this function is a Table with tokenized text data added to the input Table. The parameter settings used in the function are shown below. ##### ++Parameters++ 1. **Input Columns*** : text 2. **Hold Columns** : None 3. **New Column Prefix** : tokenized 4. **Stemming** : False 5. **Extraction** : Select All 6. **Power of Speech Tagging** : True ### Python ``` from brightics.function.textanalytics import tokenizer_eng input_table = inputs[0] result = tokenizer_eng(table=input_table, input_cols=['text'], hold_cols=None, new_col_prefix='tokenized', stemming=False, pos_extraction=None, is_tagged=True) output = result['out_table'] ```
In this python script, simple text data Table created by Create Table function are used as input of tokenizer_eng function. The output of this function is a Table with tokenized text data added to the input Table.
